Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible metabolic acidosis, and abnormal urinary losses. Low HbA1c and normal blood glucose argue against chronic hyperglycemia. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for acute or chronic kidney disease and possible tubular dysfunction.
